<div>M. Karthik Kambala, Commercial Diplomacy Officer at the British Deputy=
 High Commission, will shed light on Chevening Scholarships and Fellowships=
 for faculty members and scientists.
<br>
<br>
The talk has been arranged on <b>October 4 2016 at Hall 2, IC&amp;SR Buildi=
ng from 5.30 PM to 6.30 PM</b>.
<br>
<br>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">Abou=
t Chevening Scholarship and Fellowships:</span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbs=
p;</span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">Cheveni=
ng&nbsp; is the UK Governments International Awards Scheme aimed at develop=
ing global leaders since 1983. Funded by the Foreign and Commonwealth Offic=
e and partner organisations, Chevening offers
 two types of awards &#8211; Chevening Scholarships and Chevening Fellowshi=
ps &#8211; the recipients of which are personally selected by British Embas=
sies and High Commissions throughout the world through a rigorous selection=
 process.</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">The Che=
vening India programme is the largest in the world offering up to 65 fully =
paid scholarship and 65 fully paid fellowships every year.
</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
<br>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">Chev=
ening Masters Scholarship</span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">Cheveni=
ng Master&#8217;s scholarship programme is offered to Indian graduates with=
 at least two years' work experience. This can include voluntary work and p=
aid or unpaid internships. This is a one year
 *fully funded scholarship, available for Indian graduates in any disciplin=
e of their choice at any recognised UK university.</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">The pro=
gramme will commence from September 2017 till August 2018</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">Chev=
ening Fellowships</span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">The =
Chevening Rolls- Royce Science And Innovation Leadership Fellowship ( CRISP=
)</span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbs=
p;</span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">The Che=
vening Rolls Royce Science and Innovation Leadership Programme or CRISP as =
it is popularly known is aimed at mid-career professionals in the fields of=
 science, innovation and business. The
 fellowship will offer 14 (12 from India and 2 from Sri Lanka) senior scien=
ce and innovation professionals a 10-week study programme at the University=
 of Oxford&#8217;s Said Business School. The fully funded programme will co=
mmence in the last week of April 2017.
</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">The =
Chevening Gurukul Fellowship Programme For Leadership And Excellence</span>=
</b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">The Che=
vening Gurukul Fellowship is the UK Foreign and Commonwealth Office&#8217;s=
 flagship programme. It is India&#8217;s longest running programme.&nbsp; T=
his year we are celebrating &#8220;20 years of Gurukul&#8221;. The
 fellowship is aimed at mid-career professionals from diverse backgrounds w=
ith strong and demonstrable leadership ability. It is a twelve-week, fully =
funded residential course at King&#8217;s College London.&nbsp; Applicant s=
hould be a Citizen of India.&nbsp; Applicants should
 have a post graduate level qualification and must have at least ten years&=
#8217; work experience prior to applying with a good working knowledge of E=
nglish.
</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11pt; font-family:">The pro=
gramme will commence in the month of September 2017
</span></p>
